Kenya's Maasai Mara is among top three parks worldwide that was widely picked by travelers during the Covid-19 pandemic. This is according to the Travelers Choice in which Maasai Mara came third after Tanzania's Serengeti and India's Jim Cobertt. According to the website, travelers were attracted to the 1.3 million wildebeest in migration, with predators in hot pursuit. "It's one of the most awesome sights in nature," the website noted. The annual Travelers Choice list is arrived at from reviews, ratings, and saves that travelers share from across the globe. The information is then used to spotlight the very best.